# Theming

See also: **`design-tokens.mdc`**, **`shadcn-ui-usage.mdc`**, shadcn skill [`customization.md`](../skills/shadcn/customization.md).

Dark mode and rebranding are **token workflows** ‚Äî not per-component color overrides.

## Stack

- **Tokens** ‚Äî `src/index.css` (`:root`, `.dark`, `@theme inline`)
- **Runtime** ‚Äî `ThemeProvider` (`next-themes`) toggles `class="dark"` on `<html>`
- **Components** ‚Äî semantic classes only (`bg-background`, `text-foreground`) ‚Äî **`design-tokens.mdc`**

## ThemeProvider

`AppProviders` should wrap the app with:

```tsx
<ThemeProvider attribute="class" defaultTheme="system" enableSystem disableTransitionOnChange>
```

## User-facing theme control (required when shipping dark mode)

If `.dark` tokens exist in `index.css`, users must be able to **choose** light / dark / system ‚Äî not only inherit OS silently.

| Placement | Example |
| --------- | ------- |
| Settings page | Radio group or select |
| App header / user menu | `DropdownMenu` with theme items |
| Dev-only | OK to defer toggle **only** while dark mode is not user-facing |

**Do not** ship dark CSS variables with zero way to validate or use dark mode in the UI.

## Adding tokens (success, warning, brand accent)

Extend **`src/index.css`** ‚Äî both `:root` and `.dark` ‚Äî then `@theme inline`:

```css
:root {
  --success: oklch(0.62 0.17 145);
  --success-foreground: oklch(0.98 0.02 145);
}
.dark {
  --success: oklch(0.7 0.15 145);
  --success-foreground: oklch(0.2 0.04 145);
}
/* @theme inline: --color-success: var(--success); */
```

Use `bg-success/10 text-success` in components ‚Äî **not** `emerald-*` / `amber-*` (`design-tokens.mdc`).

## Validation workflow (before merge)

On every PR that touches UI:

1. Toggle **light** and **dark** (and **system** if supported).
2. Spot-check **2‚Äì3 representative routes** (e.g. auth, main app shell, settings) ‚Äî surfaces are often built at different times.
3. Confirm no `bg-white`, raw `slate-*`, or manual `dark:` color pairs remain.
4. Check contrast on **tinted panels** (`text-muted-foreground` on colored backgrounds may fail AA ‚Äî use `text-foreground` or a dedicated emphasis token).

## Rebrand

1. Apply shadcn preset or edit CSS variables in `index.css`.
2. Run app in light + dark.
3. Grep for violations: `slate-`, `gray-`, `bg-white`, `text-[#`, `emerald-`, `amber-`.

## Checklist

- [ ] `ThemeProvider` configured with `attribute="class"`.
- [ ] Theme toggle exists when dark tokens are used.
- [ ] New status/brand colors are CSS variables in `index.css`, not Tailwind palette classes.
- [ ] Changed screens verified in light and dark.
